Break the discipline with masturbation.

27:04.040 --> 27:06.000
Don't tell me you don't think
they masturbate now, Frank?

27:06.280 --> 27:08.720
They shouldn't be here
if they can't control themselves.

27:09.480 --> 27:11.840
We should be tougher...
keep their minds occupied.

27:12.760 --> 27:14.840
Teach them self-discipline...
that's what the rules are for!

27:15.720 --> 27:18.600
Discipline, training, to resist temptation.

27:20.720 --> 27:23.680
I think I'm going to need self-discipline
to get out of this one.

27:24.360 --> 27:28.680
- Pray, Brother, pray.
- What's so wrong with masturbation, anyway?

27:29.360 --> 27:32.760
If you don't do it yourself, well,
it comes out of its own accord.

27:34.360 --> 27:36.720
You know, for years I fought against it.

27:38.240 --> 27:40.720
All you learn is to hate your body.

27:43.600 --> 27:47.800
You know, we're old men.
Our religion is based on love.

27:48.800 --> 27:50.880
We spend the time hating ourselves.

27:52.560 --> 27:56.160
And another thing...
what if God isn't there? Heh?

27:57.760 --> 28:00.040
We'll hate ourselves then, won't we?

28:02.840 --> 28:03.800
Anybody care for a game of snooker?

28:06.800 --> 28:09.400
- There we are, Brothers!
- Dedicated to the power of prayer.

28:29.800 --> 28:30.880
Harder!

28:36.160 --> 28:37.440
Harder!

28:42.360 --> 28:44.640
Welcome to our purification, Tom!

28:45.760 --> 28:48.600
Come... bare your despicable body!

28:49.920 --> 28:51.800
Let us beat out your evils!

28:52.800 --> 28:54.160
Transcend pain with us...

28:54.400 --> 28:56.560
to a true spiritual love!

28:57.440 --> 28:58.640
You're bloody mad!

28:58.720 --> 29:00.000
Stop him, Brothers! Quick!

29:11.320 --> 29:13.520
- You better stop, Allen
- Don't tell anyone, Allen!

29:13.600 --> 29:15.080
- Head him off!
- Stop, Allen!

29:21.600 --> 29:22.640
- Secrecy {????}, Allen.
- Promise, Allen!

29:22.760 --> 29:26.120
Or we'll cover you in birds' blood.
Secrecy, Allen! Promise!

29:26.440 --> 29:27.720
- Someone's coming!
- Run!

29:28.320 --> 29:29.400
What's all the noise here?

29:31.000 --> 29:32.680
What happened to you? You all right?

29:33.800 --> 29:38.080
Oh, not them! I told you to stay away
from those fanatics, didn't I?

29:38.760 --> 29:41.440
They ought to be stopped
before they go too far. They're mad!

29:43.640 --> 29:45.440
Haven't got much to say
for yourself, have you?

29:45.640 --> 29:47.400
You nut! Come on.

29:48.600 --> 29:52.080
One! Two! Three!

29:55.000 --> 29:56.480
That's what I should do to you.

29:56.680 --> 29:59.520
The your body would be
just like your brain... frozen solid!

29:59.680 --> 30:00.720
Like yours, you mean!

30:02.240 --> 30:06.400
Wouldn't want to fall in.
Wouldn't last thirty seconds in there!

30:23.520 --> 30:25.360
Do you ever worry about dying, Fitz?

30:26.800 --> 30:27.680
No.

30:31.560 --> 30:32.840
I hope I die in a state of grace.

30:33.560 --> 30:35.520
You? State of grace?

30:36.840 --> 30:38.480
Probably die playing with yourself.

30:38.600 --> 30:40.800
- Quit it, Fitz.
- Straight to hell!

30:41.000 --> 30:42.280
Fitz!

30:42.560 --> 30:43.560
Oh, you'll be all right, mate.

30:44.640 --> 30:46.520
You're practically an angel, you're so holy.

30:48.040 --> 30:49.320
You're always in chapel.

30:50.320 --> 30:51.800
I don't know how you do it.

30:52.600 --> 30:54.160
I get sore knees and run out of words.

30:55.880 --> 30:58.560
There's only so much you can say
to someone who's not around at the time.

31:01.760 --> 31:03.640
What do you do? Say the Rosary?

31:05.520 --> 31:09.000
No... just think.

31:11.600 --> 31:13.360
It's quiet. I think.

31:16.280 --> 31:19.960
Tell Him my problems. Ask His help.

31:22.560 --> 31:26.440
Tell Him my doubts.
Do you ever doubt, Fitz?

31:27.240 --> 31:28.520
Sometimes.

31:33.720 --> 31:34.880
Hey, Scallan's gone, you know?

31:35.280 --> 31:36.760
Scallan? When?

31:37.160 --> 31:40.480
Today. Celian called him
out of class this morning.

31:41.040 --> 31:43.240
Told him to take his pin,
and that was that.

31:43.520 --> 31:44.600
Whoa. What'd he do?

31:44.920 --> 31:46.000
Don't know.

31:48.200 --> 31:49.360
He was a great bloke, though.

31:50.880 --> 31:52.960
- Pretty clean, too.
- Must have been something.

31:53.640 --> 31:54.720
We'll never know.

31:55.440 --> 31:57.720
It's really bad...
no explanations, no goodbyes.

31:58.520 --> 32:02.480
- Just take your pin.
- Maybe he chucked it in?

32:02.800 --> 32:03.560
Lost his vocation.

32:03.960 --> 32:05.560
- They'll never tell.
- Maybe he had trouble at home.

32:05.640 --> 32:09.520
Maybe. They should be able to tell us.
We're not idiots.

32:11.440 --> 32:13.000
Probably think it'll make us doubt.

32:14.000 --> 32:17.000
Yeah... cut out the rotten fruit
before it contaminates the rest.

32:17.200 --> 32:17.960
Load of rubbish.

32:18.680 --> 32:20.640
Must think our vocations are pretty weak!

32:23.360 --> 32:24.440
Just take your pin.

32:29.040 --> 32:29.920
Yeah.

32:31.720 --> 32:34.200
Quickly and quietly! Quickly and quietly!

32:35.200 --> 32:36.280
Move on quickly.

32:36.760 --> 32:38.560
- Save us a place, Mick.
- Haven't got a chance, Tom.

33:15.840 --> 33:19.040
Sorry, Turner. Hot water bottles aren't that hot.

33:19.120 --> 33:20.400
I put boiling water in it.

33:21.120 --> 33:22.400
Boiling water?

33:22.880 --> 33:24.480
Boy, it would burn your leg off.

33:24.560 --> 33:25.760
Didn't feel a thing.

33:26.040 --> 33:28.320
- I transcended it.
- Ten minutes?

33:28.640 --> 33:30.920
You kept your leg on it for ten minutes?

33:31.320 --> 33:32.480
Yeah... look!

33:33.480 --> 33:35.280
God, brother, you're mad!

33:35.560 --> 33:38.840
Perfect meditation.
With this sort of concentration,
I could achieve any spiritual state.

33:39.120 --> 33:40.520
Ecstasy.

33:41.000 --> 33:42.680
- Now I'll see if I can endure cold.
- Tom!

33:43.400 --> 33:44.360
Brother wants to see me.

33:48.760 --> 33:51.720
Be careful of following around fanatics.

33:53.160 --> 33:56.520
You keep your innocence, Tom.
Be true to yourself.

33:58.400 --> 34:03.480
You've got a smile that'll take you
half way around the world, Tom.
Don't you lose it!

34:15.679 --> 34:16.840
Slow down... you'll kill us.

34:17.440 --> 34:18.719
Well, we don't want to miss the bounce!

34:19.120 --> 34:20.520
We only get to the footie
four times a year.

34:21.000 --> 34:24.280
- Tom at full forward?
- You bet!

34:24.400 --> 34:28.159
- Great!
- I can't wait to get lost among that crowd!

34:28.719 --> 34:29.960
Normal humans again.

34:30.639 --> 34:31.719
Well, are you normal?

34:32.040 --> 34:33.320
- Freak!
- Well, almost!

34:36.320 --> 34:37.679
Hey, why don't you join us, Frank?

34:37.800 --> 34:41.679
Yeah, it'll do you good.
Have a bit of a yell, let off some steam!

34:41.760 --> 34:42.679
Perfect.

34:42.960 --> 34:44.639
I'm going to have a nice quiet day.

34:44.760 --> 34:46.040
There's a great exhibition at the museum.

34:46.840 --> 34:50.000
Oh, yeah? Well, we'll pick you up
at the post office, will we?

34:50.400 --> 34:51.400
Fine.

34:51.480 --> 34:52.560
What about six?

34:52.880 --> 34:55.040
Give or take an hour or two, knowing you.

34:55.639 --> 34:58.720
- Any chance of you being served there?
- Not much!

35:00.720 --> 35:01.840
Here, Jim!

35:04.120 --> 35:06.800
- Can't you see that? You bloody mad?
- Get off it. You're mad!

35:08.320 --> 35:09.400
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

35:09.720 --> 35:11.880
- Kick it!
- Get rid of it!

35:12.680 --> 35:14.360
Great! Great play!

35:30.440 --> 35:32.120
Hey, hey, get off him, will you?

35:45.240 --> 35:47.600
Pride, they say, Brother,
comes before the fall.

35:47.920 --> 35:49.400
I think he's hurt more than his pride.

35:51.280 --> 35:52.760
Come on, let's move it!

35:58.360 --> 36:00.360
Oh, wow, look at those!

36:01.560 --> 36:03.840
- Would she be shaved?
- I think it's painted out.

36:03.920 --> 36:05.520
Sure, it would be underneath, wouldn't it?

36:06.600 --> 36:07.600
Stop!

36:09.600 --> 36:11.160
Oh, you little bastard, Allen!

36:12.680 --> 36:14.560
- Give us my ball.
- Piss off!

36:15.560 --> 36:16.520
- Give us my ball.
- Piss off!

36:16.720 --> 36:18.000
Oh, give it to him, Westy.

36:18.320 --> 36:19.600
Give us my ball.

36:20.600 --> 36:22.560
Righto. Get it, Piss-the-bed!

36:28.160 --> 36:29.440
- I've got it all worked out.
- What?

36:29.840 --> 36:30.840
The endurance to cold.

36:32.120 --> 36:34.000
The lake... at night!

36:34.800 --> 36:36.000
Freezing!

39:00.680 --> 39:01.760
What a game, hey!

39:03.160 --> 39:05.840
The best. It was brilliant!

39:06.640 --> 39:07.840
He's the best rover in the league!

39:10.720 --> 39:13.520
Hey. Cop that!

39:18.920 --> 39:20.480
Would you like to...

39:25.800 --> 39:27.080
Give us a refill, thanks, man.

39:42.760 --> 39:46.360
Oh, this is doing me good!
Doing me good!

39:49.560 --> 39:50.720
Here's what we need.

39:54.520 --> 39:55.720
Not bad in here, is it?

39:58.120 --> 39:59.400
Had enough beers, Madge?

40:04.280 --> 40:06.560
They killed them today. Really killed them.

40:07.480 --> 40:08.760
Yeah... great match.

40:09.760 --> 40:10.840
They even beat the umpire.

40:21.240 --> 40:22.720
Come on, Jim.

40:23.000 --> 40:24.400
Let's see how we came.

40:25.280 --> 40:26.760
Come on, what are you scared of?

40:27.360 --> 40:28.640
They won't bite.

40:33.440 --> 40:34.640
Hi, girls.

40:34.840 --> 40:36.520
Oh! Hi, handsome.

40:38.120 --> 40:39.600
Mind if I join you?

40:40.000 --> 40:41.760
Please do.

40:47.680 --> 40:50.360
What about your pretty friend? He shy?

40:51.160 --> 40:52.320
A bit, yeah!

40:52.720 --> 40:54.520
- Hey, come on, Jim.
- Yeah, come on, Jim.

40:54.720 --> 40:55.920
It's all right, mate, come on.

40:56.000 --> 40:57.080
We won't eat you.

41:05.560 --> 41:06.720
Hey, Jim!

41:07.240 --> 41:10.560
I need... I need some air.
I'll see you in the car.

41:15.280 --> 41:17.600
Can't take it, these young blokes.

41:17.800 --> 41:19.000
Drink?

41:31.400 --> 41:32.960
Well... what do you girls do for a living?

41:33.080 --> 41:35.160
Oh, we work around the
corner in the factory.

41:35.440 --> 41:38.720
I'm a secretary. Madge here's in accounts.

41:40.720 --> 41:41.800
It's pretty boring.

41:42.120 --> 41:47.080
- Oh?
- We'd much rather just live it up a bit.

41:48.080 --> 41:49.160
Have a bit of fun.

41:49.680 --> 41:50.960
Yeah... a bit of fun.

41:51.440 --> 41:54.720
A few laughs, a few drinks.
Meet some interesting fellows.

41:57.840 --> 42:00.120
And what do you do
with yourself all week?

42:03.520 --> 42:04.880
I'm a schoolteacher.

42:05.200 --> 42:09.680
Oh, so you'd need a
bit of fun yourself, then.

42:10.480 --> 42:11.240
Yeah.

42:11.960 --> 42:12.840
Yeah, sure.

42:13.800 --> 42:17.800
How do you... what do you...

42:35.200 --> 42:36.400
Well, it's about time.

42:36.800 --> 42:39.560
God, Jim, they were serious.
They nearly had me.

42:40.080 --> 42:42.440
It's the last time, Jim. I promise.

42:42.640 --> 42:43.720
It's the last time.

42:44.320 --> 42:45.720
Frank will be furious.

42:45.800 --> 42:47.280
It must be really late.

42:48.280 --> 42:50.040
- Sober up.
- Yeah, OK.

42:50.560 --> 42:55.440
OK. That was too close. It was close, Jim.

43:11.760 --> 43:12.720
Slow down, Vic!

43:16.240 --> 43:17.640
Look out, you'll kill us!

43:32.840 --> 43:36.520
We're not too bad.
A few bruises, the back's a bit sore.

43:36.920 --> 43:38.200
The car must be a mess.

43:39.280 --> 43:40.680
Oh, yeah, you should see it.

43:41.960 --> 43:43.640
It's going to cost us a fortune, I'm afraid.

43:43.840 --> 43:45.320
You don't look too good.

43:45.840 --> 43:47.800
That's funny... I feel wonderful.

43:49.600 --> 43:50.800
How are the others?

43:51.400 --> 43:55.880
Well, Brother James is all right.
Francine's rather badly shaken up,
I'm afraid.

43:56.480 --> 43:58.760
We saw him go inside a minute ago.
He looked a bit strange. Isn't he...

43:58.840 --> 44:00.720
He probably didn't see us, Dear.

44:01.120 --> 44:02.200
Probably.

44:02.320 --> 44:04.680
- Hi Mom, hi Dad!
- Here's Tom. Well, I better leave you.

44:05.600 --> 44:06.560
Goodbye, Brother.

44:06.680 --> 44:07.840
Have a nice stay, Mrs. Allen.

44:08.160 --> 44:09.240
Thank you.

44:09.680 --> 44:10.800
- How about this lot.
- Hi, Tom.

44:11.120 --> 44:12.600
By golly, he's grown, hasn't he?

44:13.600 --> 44:14.600
How are you?

44:15.600 --> 44:16.680
What do you think
about your Mum staying, eh?

44:17.480 --> 44:19.680
- That be good?
- I'll say. Two weeks.

44:20.640 --> 44:22.600
It's more than a guest house.
You'll have to have a look at it.

44:22.720 --> 44:24.000
It'll do you good. Won't it, Dick?

44:24.880 --> 44:27.680
Auntie Mary's due to have a baby soon.
It might be twins.

44:27.880 --> 44:31.560
- Twins? Gee.
- They think so. She's rather large.

44:31.640 --> 44:32.560
Isn't she, Dick?

44:32.640 --> 44:33.600
Like a mountain!

44:34.600 --> 44:36.080
Here, Dear, have one of these,
something to keep you going.

44:36.280 --> 44:38.960
- I got a new bike.
- Yeah, the lucky devil!

44:39.480 --> 44:40.840
Have you? A newie?

44:41.760 --> 44:44.160
No, it's Stevie's old one, I'll fix it up.

44:49.120 --> 44:57.600
<i>Tell me I may always dance
The anniversary waltz with you.</i>

44:58.320 --> 45:07.200
<i>Tell me this is real romance
An anniversary dream come true.</i>

45:07.600 --> 45:18.560
<i>Let this be the answer to our future years
Through millions of smiles
and a few little tears.</i>

45:18.960 --> 45:29.560
<i>May I always listen to
the anniversary waltz with you.</i>

45:33.760 --> 45:34.920
God, I'm in trouble again!

45:39.680 --> 45:44.600
C = (F - 32) x 5/9

45:44.800 --> 45:47.600
He steeped himself in the
rationalism of the Enlightenment...

45:47.680 --> 45:49.480
and the romantic philosophy of Rousseau.

45:50.680 --> 45:52.640
And you'll note that it starts in a
circle at the top...

45:52.760 --> 45:54.440
those of you who listen to me
in French class...

45:54.520 --> 45:58.000
will know it's called a cirque.

46:17.200 --> 46:20.600
This is Bryan Anderson.
Bryan just started in accountancy.

46:20.680 --> 46:21.960
- Hi.
- Hi.

46:22.080 --> 46:23.240
And this is Nigel Ryan.

46:23.440 --> 46:25.840
- Nigel's an actor.
- A resting actor.

46:25.920 --> 46:26.840
- Hello.
- Hello.

46:27.320 --> 46:30.800
- And over here, Miss Doyle...
- Hello.

46:31.520 --> 46:32.480
and Miss Weatherhead.

46:32.720 --> 46:35.760
Hello. He's handsome, isn't he?

46:36.160 --> 46:38.040
Take after his father?

46:38.240 --> 46:39.120
Of course.

46:40.040 --> 46:42.120
Miss Doyle and Miss Weatherhead
are in charge of the girls...

46:42.200 --> 46:45.880
- who are here on the Christian...
- Christian Fellowship Association.

46:46.600 --> 46:47.760
Quite a job they have, too.

47:13.560 --> 47:15.640
- You know what you've been
missing out on? - Quit it, Lynnette!

47:16.840 --> 47:17.840
I think so.

47:18.040 --> 47:19.120
Aren't you a bit young to know?

47:19.320 --> 47:20.800
I'm in fourth form.

47:21.400 --> 47:23.480
- Just because you're bright doesn't mean
to say you know everything! - Quit it, Lynnette!

47:23.840 --> 47:24.720
You're only 13.

47:25.040 --> 47:27.200
Well, it's better you than me,
that's all I can say.

47:28.920 --> 47:30.800
You won't be able to get married,
have a family.

47:31.400 --> 47:33.680
There's a lot more to life than that, too!

47:35.160 --> 47:36.640
Vocation is a special thing.

47:38.560 --> 47:39.720
It's hard to explain.

47:40.720 --> 47:41.600
Not many people are so lucky.

47:43.200 --> 47:44.480
Lynnette!

47:45.800 --> 47:47.560
- Lucky!
- Hang on, Nigel.

47:48.880 --> 47:51.840
- How did you get your vocation?
- Did God send you a letter or something?

47:54.240 --> 47:55.440
Sorry.

47:55.920 --> 47:59.320
It was during Benediction. It's hard to describe.

48:00.800 --> 48:02.600
I sort of got carried away...

48:03.800 --> 48:05.680
- The atmosphere.
- Yeah.

48:07.440 --> 48:09.920
- Once removed from God.
- One thing about the Catholics,
you know...

48:10.040 --> 48:11.600
their services are pure theater.

48:12.120 --> 48:14.200
- Wonderful.
- You're a nut, Nigel.

48:15.480 --> 48:16.360
True.

48:16.560 --> 48:18.760
Lynette, you've had it...
I'm going to get you now!

48:19.040 --> 48:20.280
Girls!

48:40.040 --> 48:41.640
I'm going to get you!

48:44.320 --> 48:45.400
Given up, have you?

48:47.800 --> 48:49.080
It's so high.

48:50.400 --> 48:51.960
- That was fun.
- Yeah.

49:34.760 --> 49:42.360
<i>It's whispered to me that
you're wonderful, beautiful, heavenly</i>

49:42.440 --> 49:44.520
- <i>and that you're...</i>
- Are you singing, Allen?

49:44.640 --> 49:46.320
- Yes. Brother.
- I can't hear you.

49:47.720 --> 49:48.880
My voice has dropped, Brother.

49:49.800 --> 49:51.560
Are you sure you're not
dropping it deliberately?

49:53.080 --> 49:54.240
Yes, Brother.

49:55.560 --> 49:56.520
Yeah, well, very well, right.

49:56.720 --> 49:58.320
Well take it from the
third and fourth lines, boys.

49:58.400 --> 50:00.080
Ready? One, two, three:...

50:00.480 --> 50:04.160
<i>It's whispered...</i>
Oh, come on, come on,
why aren't you singing now?

50:04.480 --> 50:06.560
- Good morning, boys.
- Good morning, Father.

50:07.040 --> 50:08.720
I'm sorry, Father. I didn't see you there.

50:09.040 --> 50:10.000
Welcome back!

50:10.200 --> 50:11.280
It's good to be back, Brother!

50:12.200 --> 50:13.760
Well, all ready for the retreat, boys?

50:14.280 --> 50:15.160
Yes, Father.

50:15.840 --> 50:17.920
A retreat is a time for meditation.

50:18.840 --> 50:22.920
The silence isn't a hardship,
penance, it has a purpose...

50:23.000 --> 50:25.600
it's there to rid you of all distractions.

50:25.880 --> 50:27.960
So that you can think and concentrate.

50:28.480 --> 50:31.440
So that you can examine
yourselves... thoroughly.

50:32.160 --> 50:34.440
Three days' silence isn't a long time...

50:34.520 --> 50:35.720
when you consider the benefits.

50:37.200 --> 50:41.400
In the days before the retreat,
I'll be available to talk to.

50:42.200 --> 50:44.680
As you can see,
I'm quite a friendly chap,...

50:44.760 --> 50:46.840
with quite broad shoulders.

50:48.040 --> 50:51.720
If there's anyone who has any problem
he'd like to speak to me about...

50:51.920 --> 50:52.920
feel free.

50:57.720 --> 50:59.600
I find it hard sometimes, Father.

51:01.200 --> 51:04.480
I'm always in trouble for being late.
Being untidy.

51:04.560 --> 51:06.240
But you're trying, aren't you, Tom?

51:06.440 --> 51:07.640
I am trying.

51:08.440 --> 51:10.720
I'd like to make this a
vale to Our Lady if I can.

51:11.000 --> 51:12.880
Well, trying's the important thing.

51:13.200 --> 51:15.160
Keep trying, and pray to God.

51:15.480 --> 51:16.760
He'll help you.

51:16.960 --> 51:18.640
I spend a lot of time in chapel, Father.

51:18.720 --> 51:20.720
I noticed that, Tom, that's good.

51:22.000 --> 51:23.680
Anything else worrying you?

51:23.800 --> 51:27.560
Any problem you think
you can't talk to anyone about?

51:28.760 --> 51:30.040
No. Not really.

51:31.160 --> 51:32.720
You don't sound sure.

51:33.720 --> 51:36.000
You can talk to me, you know,
that's what I'm here for.

51:36.520 --> 51:37.600
To help.

51:39.000 --> 51:39.920
Nothing, really.

51:42.280 --> 51:45.640
Do you have any...
temptations you find hard to handle?

51:48.760 --> 51:51.720
- Bad thoughts, say?
- No more than normal, Father.

51:55.240 --> 51:59.680
Do you have trouble with...
playing with yourself?

52:02.520 --> 52:03.600
No, Father.

52:05.200 --> 52:06.280
That's good.

52:08.080 --> 52:10.640
I believe you have a
problem with bedwetting.

52:12.760 --> 52:14.520
I've got something here that might help.

52:15.280 --> 52:17.600
It's water from the shrine at Lourdes.

52:18.920 --> 52:20.280
Lourdes water?

52:20.800 --> 52:21.680
Really?

52:24.880 --> 52:27.560
At the invitation of Brother Gérard,...

52:31.160 --> 52:32.600
- With red hair?
- That's right!

52:32.760 --> 52:35.560
Extraordinary! I've known him for years.
I was stationed with him...

52:36.560 --> 52:38.840
...six years ago.
He runs a marvelous community.

52:39.920 --> 52:41.720
Yes, you wouldn't get away
with much with him, though.

52:42.640 --> 52:43.800
He's as tough as nails.

52:43.920 --> 52:44.880
He's got a great sense of humor, though.

52:46.880 --> 52:49.840
- Remarkable man.
- Yes, he certainly is.

52:51.760 --> 52:53.240
He's the reason I became a Brother.

52:53.440 --> 52:56.520
- Really?
- He used to teach me
when I was at school.

52:57.520 --> 52:58.800
I thought he was wonderful.

53:02.080 --> 53:03.280
You're a bit edgy tonight, Frank.

53:04.400 --> 53:08.040
My word, I'm edgy.
I very nearly lost my life
because of you and your weakness.

53:08.640 --> 53:09.600
An experience I could
well have done without.

53:09.680 --> 53:12.120
- Oh, let's not go through all that again...
- Excuse me...

53:12.400 --> 53:14.000
But we were having a pleasant evening!

53:14.880 --> 53:18.080
I don't think Father Marshall should be
subjected to our family squabbles.

53:19.880 --> 53:21.040
Sorry.

53:21.280 --> 53:24.440
Please, please, treat me as one
of the family. I enjoy it.

53:24.560 --> 53:27.520
I should think so, too. I mean, where else
could you find such wonderful company?

53:27.840 --> 53:29.080
Intellectual, witty, talented...

53:31.800 --> 53:33.880
That was a rather nice piece
you were playing then, Brother.

53:34.000 --> 53:36.440
Perhaps Father Marshall
would like to hear some more?

53:37.160 --> 53:39.400
- Marvelous!
- Yes, more please!

53:57.560 --> 53:58.520
How are the studies, James?

54:00.720 --> 54:02.320
Oh, managing.

54:03.120 --> 54:04.480
Managing!? He loves it!

54:05.280 --> 54:06.640
He's going to do very well, I think.

54:12.480 --> 54:15.520
You really love all this...
brotherhood, don't you?

54:18.040 --> 54:18.920
Yes, I do.

54:22.040 --> 54:23.280
I belong here.

54:26.000 --> 54:27.280
Part of a community.

54:31.880 --> 54:33.560
Oh, I've got my weaknesses.

54:34.080 --> 54:35.240
As he knows.

54:38.760 --> 54:39.920
There's a lot here that troubles me.

54:41.920 --> 54:43.520
A lot of things I don't agree with, but...

54:44.720 --> 54:46.560
I'm a grass reed... I'll go with it.

54:48.280 --> 54:49.960
Hopefully, I can affect
some changes for the good.

54:56.960 --> 54:58.560
I'm good with the boys.

55:00.840 --> 55:03.600
I don't know...
it's a pretty hard thing to explain, really.

55:08.040 --> 55:10.880
- I'm off to bed. Good night.
- Good night, Brother.

55:17.320 --> 55:19.680
Maybe it's because
we're one big happy family.

55:25.000 --> 55:28.080
Hey, Tom. Would you like to go
for a walk with us girls?

55:28.560 --> 55:29.440
Do you mind, Mom?

55:29.560 --> 55:30.840
